"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-06-paris-olympics-2024-france-to-play-spain-in-mens-football-final\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  France will play Spain for the gold medal in the men's football event at the 2024 Olympics.  The hosts came from behind to defeat Egypt 3-1 in the second semi-final of the competition.  Mahmoud Saber opened the scoring in the second half, before Jean-Phillipe Mateta equalized late in the game.  Mateta put France ahead in extra time, before Michael Olise capped off the win with a smart finish.  In the first semi-final, Juanlu Sanchez grabbed an 85th minute winner, to seal a 2-1 win over Morocco.  Morocco led 1-0 at half-time, after Soufiane Rahimi converted a penalty in the 37th minute.  Spain levelled in the 65th after Fermin Lopez fired a left-footed shot low into the bottom corner.  Kolimba set to sign new contract at Katsina United  Paris Olympics Games: Low preparation, other issues mar Team Nigeria's early showing  UK, France, Germany 'under threat' from Iranian missiles - Israel  Israel-US war in Iran illegal, causing damage to civilians - Spain's PM Sanchez  War: Not acceptable to attack France - Macron warns Iranian President  France calls for immediate de-escalation of war in Lebanon  Russia warns UK, France after deadly Ukraine strike  Spain's PM Sanchez urges end to UN Security Council veto power, blasts US for global conflicts  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"